HEADWORD: Sabadilla
<hw>Sab`a*dil"la</hw> <pr>(s⟦acr⟧b`⟦adot⟧*d⟦icr⟧l"l⟦adot⟧)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp. <ets>cebadilla</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A Mexican liliaceous plant (<spn>Schoenocaulon officinale</spn>);
also, its seeds, which contain the alkaloid <prod>veratrine</prod>. It
was formerly used in medicine as an emetic and purgative.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sabaean</ent>⟦br⟧
